What's going on here?? something's wrong with this picture...I may not have had the chance to play too much, but DAMN IT! i played as much if not longer then my other friends(fiends as i like to call them now :P).<br>
I love my Wizard...likes so many people mentioned before, I love blowing things up to shreads.  But after 10min of meditation to FM, it sucks that i can't even kill a blue cause half of my spell is resisted.<br>
Is it me? am I just a bad wizard? <br>
In DL I remember dumping mana so i could save a groupmate from a certain doom, I snared, rooted and blasted the hell out of the thing.  But you know who got the credit for it? the cleric.../sigh<br>
I stupified the mob from 100%hp to 2%hp but the thanks went to the cleric, saying &quot;Thank God you healed me in time!&quot; followed by &quot;w00t&quot; &quot;/shout we have the best cleric in the game!&quot; OMFG!!! I couldn't face myself to tell them that i killed the thing, I didn't want to be labeled as a &quot;Glory Hog&quot; but DAMN IT! I contributed too! /shrug.../sigh.../sigh.../cry<br>
I actually had a group kick me out to make room for the chanter, then reinvite me cause the chanter found another group...how do I know this? cause they told me! I don't think WE as Wizards ask too much...just enough mana and dmg for World Domination...is that too much??? /grins evily<br>
I still keep thinking back to the day when i made my first character, trying to decide chanter or wizard?  hmm...Holy Shit! dmg unmatched by any other class? I'm THERE!  now it's &quot;arcane transportation&quot;(btw did they impliment that dialog to discription for wizards on the manuals yet?) BAH! BAH you all to hell!<br>
But you know what the worst part is? even tho I have a twink monk and a chanter, I still can't retire my Wizard...I have a wall paper of her in my laptop and every time i turn it on, i still remember being excited to play her.../sigh<br>
For those of you still reading this, I'm sorry it was so long.  <br>
Anyways, I just hit 42 last night and I'm so proud of my Wizard still striving for the end, even after all the deaths and rejection she has been through...<br>
<br>
For those of you not happy with your Wizard class, do what I did and make a wall paper and look at it long and hard...and maybe you'll see why YOU play this class.  After all, it was your first pick right? if it wasn't, BAH you too!<br>
